project TopologicalSort

task DeterministicTopologicalSort
    goal
        Topologically sort a dependency graph, dependencies first, using deterministic tie-breaking.
    input
        deps
    output
        order
    constraint
        Function name is topo_sort.
        Module is impl.py.
        Return value is a list.
        deps is a dict mapping node to list of nodes it depends on.
        Nodes referenced only as a dependency are treated as having no deps.
        Ties are broken by alphabetical order (sorted candidates).
    test
        An empty dict returns an empty list.
        A single node with no deps returns that node.
        A depends on B yields B then A.
        A chain A->B->C returns C, B, A.
        A diamond: A depends on B and C, B and C depend on D returns D, B, C, A.
        A dependency on an implicit leaf still resolves.
        Two independent nodes sort alphabetically.
        A cycle raises ValueError.
        A self-loop raises ValueError.
        Non-dict input raises TypeError.
    success
        Every acceptance case above matches exactly.
